rg/\">Maternal Wellness Center</a> (MWC) Timmy and I are super excited about cloth diapering. Cloth diapering has come a long way from safety pins and cloth (that\'s what my mommy used on me!)\n\nApart from it potentially saving us at least $5000 (that\'s if we cloth diaper two kids... and I\'m not exaggerating with that number) I\'m also excited about what it means for our impact on the environment. Knowing that 600 of my child\'s dirty diapers could be sitting in some landfill and will take generations and generations to decompose really bothers me. The number is just too real. I can picture that.\n\nWe found a class being taught at the MWC back in July and found it extremely informative and helpful. We had no idea there were so many options! Timmy was able to snap a shot of the class:\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_333\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"256\" caption=\"This is me in the car getting ready to head into the class.\"]<a href=\"http://burningones.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/jen-teaching.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-333\" title=\"Class\" src=\"http://burningones.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/jen-teaching-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"The instructor, Jen, talking about diapers.\" width=\"256\" height=\"191\" /></a></dt> </dl></div>\nI thought a bit about doing Elimination Communication (otherwise known as infant potty-training) but I am WAY too excited about using these cute little diapers that for me its totally worth the extra work. After getting some of our supplies at our baby shower (yay!) I\'m picking the rest up on Wednesday.\n\nI know these pictures are REALLY old (I was around six months) but these are of the day we went to the cloth diapering class.\n<div class=\"mceTemp\"><dl id=\"attachment_332\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" style=\"width: 229px;\"> <dt class=\"wp-caption-dt\"><a href=\"http://burningones.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/me-in-the-car.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-332\" title=\"Me in the car\" src=\"http://burningones.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/me-in-the-car-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"Getting ready to head inside.\" width=\"219\" height=\"163\" /></a>[/caption]','We\'re Cloth Diapering!',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2008-09-16 20:34:34','2008-09-17 00:34:34','',0,'http://burningones.com/?p=291',0,'post','',0),(292,2,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Perspectives on Consumable Media Part 1: What Is It?',0,'','inherit','open','open','','168-revision','','','2008-08-13 17:25:39','2008-08-13 21:25:39','',168,'http://burningones.com/1999/11/30/168-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(293,2,'2008-08-13 17:32:46','2008-08-13 21:32:46','Research Topics:\nInformation Age, First World Problems\n\nOutline:\nIntroduction\nDefinition of Consumable Media\nTypes and Examples of Consumable Media\nIncorrect Media Associations\nMagazines, Video Rentals, Libraries, Books, Etc.\nConclusion w/ reference to Part 2 of the 3 parter','Perspectives on Consumable Media Part 1: What Is It?',0,'Media that costs nothing, is interesting but not necessary, and comes in large volumes is a first-world problem that has rapidly grown since the introduction of the internet.  I\'m proposing that a good title for this is Consumable Media and needs its own set of triage rules in order to deal with it (if you really want to deal with it at all).','inherit','open','open','','168-revision-2','','','2008-08-13 17:32:46','2008-08-13 21:32:46','',168,'http://burningones.com/2008/08/13/168-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(294,2,'2008-08-13 17:43:28','2008-08-13 21:43:28','Outline:\nIntroduction\n    The effects of the Information Age\n    Generation-Y and Z\n    The attractiveness of information\nDefinition of Consumable Media\n    Consumable media is provided free of charge, interests you but is not required content for you to master, and comes in large volumes.  In addendum, it is more than likely archived \nTypes and Examples of Consumable Media\nIncorrect Media Associations\n    Magazines, Video Rentals,